[1] China update
Date: Sat 25 Jan 2020
Source: Chinese National Health Committee [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqfkdt/202001/a7cf0437d1324aed9cc1b890b8ee29e6.shtml


Update on pneumonia of new coronavirus infection as of 24:00 on 24 Jan 2020
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
At 04:00 on [24 Jan 2020], 29 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) reported 444 new confirmed cases and 16 new deaths. Three new cases were cured and discharged. A total of 19 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) reported 1118 new suspected cases; 30 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) reported the epidemic situation, and Qinghai Province was newly added.

As of 24:00 on [24 Jan 2020], the Health and Health Commission received a total of 1287 confirmed cases of pneumonia with new coronavirus infection in 29 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities), including 237 severe cases and 41 deaths (39 cases in Hubei Province, [1 case in Hebei Province and 1 case in Heilongjiang]); 38 cases have been cured and discharged. A total of 1965 suspected cases were reported in 20 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities).

At present, 15 197 close contacts have been traced, 1230 medical observations have been lifted, and 13 967 people are still receiving medical observations.

In addition, confirmed cases were reported abroad: 5 cases in Hong Kong, China, 2 cases in Macau, 3 cases in Taiwan, 4 cases in Thailand (2 cases have been cured), 2 cases in Japan (1 case has been cured), 2 cases in Korea, 2 cases were in the USA, 2 in Viet Nam, 3 in Singapore, 1 in Nepal, and 2 in France.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In yesterday's (24 Jan 2020) update, there were 259 new confirmed cases and 8 new deaths from the 29 provinces; today's figures are 444 new confirmed cases and 16 new deaths. Likewise there were 830 confirmed cases of pneumonia in 29 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities), including 177 severe cases and 25 deaths (24 in Hubei Province and 1 in Hebei Province). There were a total of 1072 suspected cases. In contrast, today (25 Jan 2020) there were a total of 1287 confirmed cases of pneumonia in 29 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities), including 237 severe cases and 41 deaths (39 in Hubei Province, 1 Hebei Province, and 1 in Heilongjiang Province). There were a total of 1965 suspected cases were reported in 20 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities). Media and social media reports have markedly elevated estimates, one speculating that there have been 100 000 cases in Wuhan. There appears to be significant person-to-person transmission ongoing within this outbreak, and cases are occurring almost throughout China (in 29 of the 33 provinces).

A good map of China showing the provinces can be found at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html. Note that one of the new fatalities was in Heilongjiang Province in the extreme northeast of the country. - Mod.MPP]

[In related news, a 62-year-old doctor and ENT specialist at Hubei Xinhua hospital in Wuhan is apparently the first known fatality among staff treating patients. See https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/jan/25/coronavirus-outbreak-doctor-in-wuhan-hospital-dies-as-army-medics-flown-in. -Mod.LXL]

