- Nepal ex China
Date: Fri 24 Jan 2020
Source: Straits Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/south-asia/wuhan-virus-nepal-confirms-first-case-of-new-coronavirus


A Nepali student home from China tested positive for the new coronavirus, an official in Kathmandu said on Friday ([24 Jan 2020]), making it the 1st confirmed case in the Himalayan nation.

"One patient tested positive for coronavirus. He is a Nepali student studying in China," Mahendra Shrestha, a Health Ministry spokesperson, told Reuters.

The student had come home on holiday from Wuhan in China, a ministry of health statement said.

