[8] More cases in countries with prior importations

- USA ex Wuhan, China, 2nd case confirmed; Chicago. Submitted by Mary Marshall <mjm2020@googlemail.com>

- South Korean authorities confirmed Friday [24 Jan 2020] that a 2nd person has tested positive for the new coronavirus. The 55-year-old South Korean man had been living in Wuhan and had landed at Gimpo Airport in Seoul on a flight from Shanghai. He is now hospitalized. Submitted by ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

- Japan also confirmed a 2nd and a 3rd case. The 2nd case is a man in his 40s from Wuhan who arrived in Japan on Sunday [19 Jan 2020] on a flight through Hong Kong. He is currently being treated, the Health Ministry said. The 3rd case is a woman in her 30's, and a resident of Wuhan, who by self-report had not stopped by the seafood market in Wuhan. She came to Japan on January 18 (no symptoms at this time). Fever and cough appeared on the night of January 21. She visited a medical institution in Tokyo on January 23. Submitted by ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

- 5th confirmed case in Thailand, Chinese tourist from Wuhan. Submitted by John Cathey <jt.cathey@gmail.com>. Thailand's 6th confirmed case of coronavirus,a Chinese tourist in Hua Hin. https://forum.thaivisa.com/topic/1145125-chinese-tourist-in-hua-hin-confirmed-as-thailand%E2%80%99s-sixth-case-of-coronavirus/. Submitted by ProMED-MBDS moderator Yin Myo Aye.

- Total of 3 coronavirus cases confirmed in Taiwan: Local news outlet via Focus Taiwan.

